    "name": "Monte Carlo global sensitivity analysis for VAD hemolysis CFD predictions",
    "description": "A Sobol-index global sensitivity analysis was conducted over 10,000 Latin-hypercube samples varying inlet flow rate (±15%), rotor speed (±5%), blood viscosity (±12%), and the power-law hemolysis model exponents (α: ±20%, β: ±18%). Results identified rotor speed and the hemolysis model exponent α as dominant contributors, together accounting for 68% of output variance in predicted Normalized Index of Hemolysis (NIH); inlet flow rate contributed 22%, with blood viscosity and β-exponent contributing the remainder. This ranking was stable across all five operating-point combinations evaluated in COU2.",
    "method": "Sobol variance decomposition (Saltelli 2002) via SALib v1.4",
    "dominantFactors": [
      "rotor speed",
      "hemolysis power-law exponent alpha"
    ],
    "sampleSize": 10000
  },
