      "name": "In-scope domain constraint for COU2 VAD hemolysis assessment",
      "description": "The model is applicable only to single-stage centrifugal blood pumps with impeller tip diameter 30–52 mm operating with human whole blood (hematocrit 35–45%). Predictions are scoped to the FDA generic pump geometry; extrapolation to axial-flow or pulsatile-flow devices is explicitly excluded. Patient population is restricted to adult chronic heart-failure patients (BSA 1.5–2.2 m²). Blood damage models calibrated on bovine blood are flagged as out-of-scope without additional species-correction validation."
    },
